00:17:55.579 --> 00:17:59.020
this is Linux or Ubuntu.

00:17:59.020 --> 00:18:02.260
And then the different rows are the different R versions.

00:18:02.260 --> 00:18:06.239
There's actually a lot of issues right now with R35, because a lot of people are depending

00:18:06.239 --> 00:18:08.359
on R36 or higher.

00:18:08.359 --> 00:18:09.939
So we're currently not testing there.

00:18:09.939 --> 00:18:13.979
I know I kind of like 2,500 plus, so it's more like 2,000 plus.

00:18:13.979 --> 00:18:18.260
But I still think it holds, where once the next R version comes out, it will go back

00:18:18.260 --> 00:18:23.020
to 2,500 apps every night.

00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:25.579
And then also exposes like failure logs, things like that.

00:18:25.579 --> 00:18:27.579
